item.title: Updater Output
item.dc:creator: @abraham2119 abraham2119
item.description:
@abraham2119 wrote:

317 nodelist ran through moparisthebest’s aryan-updater:

[code]public final class NodeList {

public NodeList() {
    head = new Node();
    head.prev = head;
    head.next = head;
}

public void insertHead(Node node) {
    if (node.next != null)
        node.unlink();
    node.next = head.next;
    node.prev = head;
    node.next.prev = node;
    node.prev.next = node;
}

public void insertTail(Node node) {
    if (node.next != null)
        node.unlink();
    node.next = head;
    node.prev = head.prev;
    node.next.prev = node;
    node.prev.next = node;
}

public Node popHead() {
    Node node = head.prev;
    if (node == head) {
        return null;
    } else {
        node.unlink();
        return node;
    }
}

public Node reverseGetFirst() {
    Node node = head.prev;
    if (node == head) {
        current = null;
        return null;
    } else {
        current = node.prev;
        return node;
    }
}

public Node getFirst() {
    Node node = head.next;
    if (node == head) {
        current = null;
        return null;
    } else {
        current = node.next;
        return node;
    }
}

public Node reverseGetNext() {
    Node node = current;
    if (node == head) {
        current = null;
        return null;
    } else {
        current = node.prev;
        return node;
    }
}

public Node getNext() {
    Node node = current;
    if (node == head) {
        current = null;
        return null;
    }
    current = node.next;
    return node;
}

public void removeAll() {
    if (head.prev == head)
        return;
    do {
        Node node = head.prev;
        if (node == head)
            return;
        node.unlink();
    } while (true);
}

private final Node head;
private Node current;

}
[/code]

edit: and your nodelist does not match up with the current one, because if ‘c’ is ‘next’ and ‘e’ is ‘previous’ as you say, then your ‘insertFront’ function should be:

final void insertFront(Node node) { if(node.previous != null) { node.unlink(); } node.next = head; node.previous = head.previous; node.previous.next = node; node.next.previous = node; } NOT

final void insertFront(Node node) { if (node.prev != null) { node.unlink(); } node.next = head.next; node.prev = head; node.prev.next = node; node.next.prev = node; }

item.title: Updater Output
item.dc:creator: @Metho_D Method
item.description:
@Metho_D wrote:

just because a client is “refactored” doesn’t mean it’s refactored correctly…

here is my deque (nodelist) class from the current client (#578). unless they iterate through a list backwards for some reason, this should be correct.

[code]final class Deque {

Node head;
private Node current;

final void insertBack(Node node) {
	if (node.prev != null) {
		node.unlink();
	}
	node.next = head;
	node.prev = head.prev;
	node.prev.next = node;
	node.next.prev = node;
}

final void merge(Deque deque) {
	mergeInternal(deque, head.next);
}

final int size() {
	int i = 0;
	for (Node node = head.next; head != node;) {
		node = node.next;
		i++;
	}

	return i;
}

final void clear() {
	do {
		Node node = head.next;
		if (node == head) {
			break;
		}
		node.unlink();
	} while (true);
	current = null;
}

final void insertFront(Node node) {
	if (node.prev != null) {
		node.unlink();
	}
	node.next = head.next;
	node.prev = head;
	node.prev.next = node;
	node.next.prev = node;
}

private final void mergeInternal(Deque deque, Node front) {
	Node back = head.prev;
	head.prev = front.prev;
	front.prev.next = head;
	if (front != head) {
		front.prev = deque.head.prev;
		front.prev.next = front;
		deque.head.prev = back;
		back.next = deque.head;
	}
}

final Node getPrev() {
	Node node = current;
	if (head == node) {
		current = null;
		return null;
	}
	current = node.prev;
	return node;
}

final Node getBack() {
	Node node = head.prev;
	if (node == head) {
		current = null;
		return null;
	} else {
		current = node.prev;
		return node;
	}
}

final Node popFront() {
	Node node = head.next;
	if (head == node) {
		return null;
	}
	node.unlink();
	return node;
}

final boolean isEmpty() {
	return head == head.next;
}

public Deque() {
	head = new Node();
	head.prev = head;
	head.next = head;
}

final Node getFront() {
	Node node = head.next;
	if (node == head) {
		current = null;
		return null;
	} else {
		current = node.next;
		return node;
	}
}

final Node getNext() {
	Node node = current;
	if (node == head) {
		current = null;
		return null;
	} else {
		current = node.next;
		return node;
	}
}

}
[/code]
